<HEADLINE> Xinhua International News Summary at 1530 GMT, March 31 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. President Bill Clinton has picked Army
General Wesley Clark to become the next top commander of the North
Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO), a local newspaper reported
Monday.
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- The four-day foreign secretary level talks between
India and Pakistan ended here Monday with no concrete results
announced, but the two sides agreed to continue their discussions
in Islamabad on dates to be mutually decided, according to Press
Trust of India.
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Iraq has decided to start food distribution as of
next month in accordance with the implementation of an
oil-for-food deal with the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Foreign Minister David Levy said Monday
that the Arab foreign ministers' decision on Sunday can only be
harmful to the peace process, the state-run Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Arab countries have hailed the draft resolution
approved Sunday night at the meeting of Arab League Council that
called for suspending Arab normalization of relations with Israel.
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- Qiao Shi, chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress (NPC) of China, ended a six-day
official visit in France and left Paris this morning. 
</P>
