<HEADLINE> GCC Secretary General Arrives in UAE </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Secretary General of the Gulf
Cooperation Council (GCC) Jamil al-Hojeilan arrived here this
evening from Doha, the capital of Qatar, on a visit to the United
Arab Emirates (UAE).
</P>
<P>
According to well-informed sources here, al-Hojeilan's visit to
the UAE is taking place within the framework of his tour of the GCC
member states in a bid to review the measures being taken by the
member states in implementing the resolutions adopted by the GCC
summit last December in Doha.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here from Doha said the GCC secretary general
today held talks with Qatari Emir Sheikh Hamad Ben Khalifa Al
Thani on the work of the GCC.
</P>
<P>
The GCC groups Bahrain, Kuwait, Qatar, Oman, Saudi Arabia and
the UAE.


