<HEADLINE> Indian PM Asked to Seek Confidence Vote by April 11 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Indian President Shankar Dayal
Sharma today asked Prime Minister H.D. Deve Gowda to prove his
majority in Lok Sabha (the lower house of parliament) by April 11,
Press Trust of India said.
</P>
<P>
Sharma, who had earlier given time till April 7 for Gowda to
seek a vote of confidence, extended the time by four days
following a request by the prime minister in view of the
Non-Aligned Movement foreign ministers' meeting to be held here on
April 6-7 and the New Year's celebrations on April 8 and 9
according to the Hindu calendar, a communique issued by the
presidential palace said.
</P>
<P>
Gowda called on the president this evening after attending a
meeting of the United Front Steering Committee where front leaders
affirmed faith in the prime minister's leadership following the
Congress party's withdrawal of support to the 14-party ruling
coalition.  
</P>
