<HEADLINE> Seminar on Child Protection in Africa Opens in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 31 (Xinhua) -- The first seminar on the
protection of the child and elimination of child labor in Africa
opened today in Arusha, Tanzania, a press release from the
Organization of African Unity (OAU) said today.
</P>
<P>
The release said the seminar will discuss the plight of
millions of African children whose lives were a daily struggle for
survival by working in violation of national legislation and
international labor standards and often in conditions harmful to
their physical, mental, spiritual and moral development.
</P>
<P>
The protection of children from work and at work is one of the
cardinal principles and concerns of the OAU and the 16th OAU
summit in Liberia in 1979 adopted a declaration for promoting the
protection of the rights and welfare of African children, said
the release.
</P>
<P>
The four-day seminar is expected to adopt a declaration and
program of action presented by the assembly of heads of state and
governments.
</P>
<P>
The seminar was held ahead of the International Conference on
Child Labor to be convened by the International Labor
Organization in Oslo, Norway in October 1997, the release added.
