<HEADLINE> Le Pen Claims "Historic Mission" of Extreme Right Party </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Jean-Marie Le Pen, the president of
France's extreme-right National Front (FN) party, today claimed a
"historic mission toward France and the Frenchmen" by his party
and made a violent attack on the government and all political
establishments of the country.
</P>
<P>
In a speech at the closing of the 10th FN national congress
today in Strasbourg, Le Pen said that he was "meditating" on the
"historic model" with which General Charles de Gaulle replaced
the 4th Republic of France with the 5th Republic.
</P>
<P>
The 68-year-old FN president ended his one-hour-and-a-half
speech with "Vive the 6th Republic !" according to the Agence
France-Presse (AFP).
</P>
<P>
"Fifty years ago, in Strasbourg, General de Gaulle appealed
for the rally of the French people against the regime of the
parties. His efforts failed. But several years later, he founded
the 5th Republic on the debris of the 4th (Republic). This is a
historic model that many should meditate," AFP quoted Le Pen as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Le Pen was re-elected president of FN by presenting himself as
the single candidate for the post on Sunday, the second day of the
national congress which triggered a large-scale protest on
Saturday by more than 50,000 people in Strasbourg.
</P>
<P>
Claiming himself as "neither racist nor anti-Semite," Le Pen
said, "We don't accept to be aggressed or insulted by anyone, no
matter whites or Catholics, Jews or blacks, crooks or
scribblers."
</P>
<P>
On the financial scandals of the country, including that of the
Credit Lyonnais, Le Pen said that the bank is "the cave of 400
thiefs" who stole 8,000 to 10,000 francs from each French family.
</P>
<P>
He recalled that under the old regimes, the ministers of
finances were often hanged. 
</P>
