Public Works Abdul Aziz Meziane and Japanese Ambassador in Rabat
Nakamutu Takashi, Japan will finance 196 preparatory systems
necessary for the provision of potable water in several provinces
in central Morocco.
</P>
<P>
Japan financed the first stage of the project in 1995 with a
grant amounting to some 2.8 million dollars. The first phase of
the project provided 86 villages with potable water. 
