<HEADLINE> Construction of Kunming Airport Extension Project Begins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Construction of the extension
project of Kunming Airport, a State Council-approved major
construction project during the 1996-2000 period, began here today.
</P>
<P>
Situated in the southern suburb of Kunming, capital of
southwest China's Yunnan Province, the airport is the main airport
in southwest China and an air transportation hub of Yunnan.
</P>
<P>
With the completion of the expansion work, the airport will be
able to handle seven million passengers and 100,000 tons of goods
annually, according to an airport authority.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that in 1996, the airport handled 4.01 million
passengers and 58,300 tons of goods.
</P>
<P>
At present, the floor space of the Kunming airport terminal
is 17,000 square meters, and that of its warehouse
is 2,200 square meters. It has four boarding gates and a
handling capacity of two million passengers.
</P>
<P>
This can not meet the need of the province's economic
development, especially for the world horticulture exposition to
be held from May 1 to October 31 in 1999, which is expected to
attract eight to ten million tourists.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the extension project will not affect the
regular air service of the airport, according to project sources.
</P>
</TEXT>
