<HEADLINE> ING International to Integrate With Barings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The Dutch ING Bank International
is to integrate with its sister bank ING Barings of London and the
new company will be called ING Barings.
</P>
<P>
An ING spokesman was quoted by today's Het Financieele Dagblad,
a Dutch newspaper, as saying that ING was making the move to meet
customers' wishes that the bank had a single profile.
</P>
<P>
"This follows developments in the past two years during which
many units were combined. We are going to make this visible now in
the organizational structure," he said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, an ING spokesman denied reports by another newspaper
De Volkskrant that the integration was due to disappointing
results at Barings.
</P>
<P>
He said that "Barings contributed more to group earnings last
year than it did in 1995. Gross earnings were more than 100
million florin (about 52.6 million U.S. dollars), and we are
pleased. All Barings operations have contributed to profit."
</P>
<P>
Het Financieele Dagblad reported that the integration includes
setting up a single treasury, trading and sales group as well as
one global risk management and global clients departments.
</P>
<P>
About 9,000 people are employed by the bank and the number is
expected to grow, it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
