<P>
"Hong Kong's return to the motherland is not only a grand
moment for Hong Kong compatriots, but also a great day for all
the Chinese people including those living in Macao," he
said. "Macao can learn a lot from Hong Kong's return and be
encouraged by that event."
</P>
<P>
The committee will help organize celebration activities in
Macao. It will also mobilize Macao citizens to attend all kinds of
celebration activities to be held around Hong Kong's return.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that celebrations will help people know more about the
great idea of 'one country, two systems' and the Macao Basic Law,"
Ma said. "We hope they will help build up confidence among local
citizens in the future of Macao." 
</P>
</TEXT>
