<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Manufacturing Output Up 0.2 Percent in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The manufacturing output of the
European Union rose by 0.2 percent in 1996, the EU's statistical
office Eurostat said today.
</P>
<P>
Germany recorded a 0.2 percent increase, but Italy suffered a
2.8 percent plunge.
</P>
<P>
In December 1996, the producer prices of the manufacturing
industry in the EU rose 0.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
The prices dropped in Germany (0.3 percent), Finland and the
United Kingdom, but rose in Italy (0.5 percent), France (0.6
percent) and Spain (1.8 percent).
</P>
<P>
The EU's manufacturing output growth has slowed down since the
last quarter of 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
