<HEADLINE> Volunteers To Help Wild Goose Realize Dreams of Parenthood </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 1 (Xinhua) -- More than 200 university students
hope to make dreams of parenthood come true for a gosling-less
pair of wild geese.
</P>
<P>
Every March since 1993, the goose couple flies into Zizhuyuan
Park in Beijing, stays for several months, befriends many of the
park's regular visitors, then flies south in the fall.
</P>
<P>
Year after year, according to park watchers, the couple's eggs
fall from the nest or are broken.
</P>
<P>
This year, when the geese arrived for their fifth park stay,
more than 200 students from the China Forestry University in
Beijing volunteered to nest-watch 'round-the-clock, and last
Sunday pitched a tent near the hatching site.
</P>
<P>
"We will take turns working around the clock until the baby
geese are hatched," said Yanjun, one of the volunteers.
</P>
<P>
As a result of the improvement in ecological environment, the
capital city has become home to more and more wild birds. On March
27, a wild swan flew into the city's Qingnianhu Park, after a
group of swans settled at a reservior in the suburbs. Endiem

nnnn
</P>
</TEXT>
