<HEADLINE> Yemeni President Denounces Shooting Incident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Yemeni President Ali Abdullah Saleh
today denounced the random shooting incident Sunday, which
left eight people killed and 11 others injured.
</P>
<P>
The president expressed sympathy and sorrow for the victims
during a visit to the Thawra public hospital to comfort the
injured of the brutal crime committed by Hassan Ali al-Baadani at
two schools in Sanaa, the capital of Yemen.
</P>
<P>
The victims include a number of children, two school teachers
and several citizens.
</P>
<P>
President Saleh has also issued a directive to grant families
of the victims sums of money as well as the treatment of the
injured at state expense, including the ones who will require
treatment abroad.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a Sanaa court has sentenced the culprit to death,
the quickest sentence ever to be passed in the history of Yemeni
justice. 
</P>
</TEXT>
