<HEADLINE> Cyprus Commemorates Liberation Struggle for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus today commemorated the
42nd anniversary of the struggle to rid the island of British
colonial rule, which ended with the independence of Cyprus in 1960.
</P>
<P>
A church service was held at Saint John's Cathedral,
officiated by the Primate of the Church of Cyprus, Archbishop
Chrysostomos, and attended by Cypriot President Glafcos Clerides,
government officials and political leaders.
</P>
<P>
In his address, Interior Minister Dinos Michaelides praised
the EOKA (National Organization of Cypriot Fighters) struggle. He
said that the struggle for freedom and justice in Cyprus will
continue with courage and patience.
</P>
<P>
Greek Cypriots will never give up their rights and will fight
until they achieve a permanent and viable solution to the Cyprus
problem, the minister stressed.
</P>
<P>
After the church service, Archbishop Chrysostomos led a prayer
at the graves of 13 fighters killed during the 1955-59 EOKA
struggle, where President Clerides laid a wreath.
</P>
<P>
Commemoration services were also held in other towns in the
Cypriot government controlled areas.
</P>
<P>
Greek Cypriot political parties have called on Greek Cypriots
to be unified in their struggle for the reunification of the
island, which remains divided since 1974 after Turkish
invasion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
