<HEADLINE> India's Congress Party, UF Hold Talks on Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Negotiations are going on
between the Congress party and the ruling United Front in a bid to
defuse the political crisis arising from the former's decision to
withdraw support to the government, Press Trust of India (PTI)
reported today.
</P>
<P>
All India Congress Committee (AICC) General Secretary Meira
Kumar told reporters today that the negotiations were taking
place, but he declined to say at what level the talks were
continuing.
</P>
<P>
Asked whether Congress party President Sitaram Kesri himself
was negotiating with the United Front or he had deputed somebody
else, Kumar said, "I cannot say at what level it is there. But
negotiations are on."
</P>
<P>
On the possibility of a snap poll in the country, Kumar said,
"The Congress party has already staked its claim to form a
government at the center and we are confident that we will form
the government. We enjoy a majority support."
</P>
<P>
The Congress party withdrew its support to the 10-month-old
United Front government led by Prime Minister H.D. Deve Gowda on
Sunday, reducing it to a minority coalition.  
</P>
</TEXT>
