<HEADLINE> HK Post Office Accepts Electronic Money for Postage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's Post Office has
announced that it will begin accepting Mondex, electronic money,
for postage payment in its Taikooshing and Shatin Central Post
Offices starting today.
</P>
<P>
Robert Footman, postmaster general, said that this new
initiative is consistent with the Mission and Vision of the Post
Office to continuously improve its service to meet the changing
market demands.
</P>
<P>
He said the introduction of Mondex reflects the Post Office's
on-going commitment to adopting new technologies and upgrading its
service, in line with the trends towards electronic commerce.
</P>
<P>
Neil Hockaday, senior manager for Card Products Division at the
 Hongkong and Shanghai Banking Corporation Limited, said that it
is certain that Mondex can help merchants shorten turnaround time
at the counter thereby offering quicker service and shorter
queuing time.
</P>
<P>
In addition to accepting Mondex at the Taikooshing and Shatin
Central Post Offices, Hong Kong Post Office will also start
accepting credit cards effective today in 49 post offices
throughout Hong Kong. 
