<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Construction Value for 1996 Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The gross value of construction
work performed by main contractors amounted to 116 billion HK
dollars (14.96 billion US dollars) in nominal terms in 1996, an
increase of 16.3 percent over 1995.
</P>
<P>
According to the Quarterly Survey of Construction Output
released today by the Census and Statistics Department, the gross
value of construction work, measured at constant market price and
performed by main contractors in 1996, increased by 9 percent
compared with 1995.
</P>
<P>
The gross value of construction work performed at public sector
sites amounted to 46.7 billion HK dollars (6.03 billion US
dollars), representing an increase of 23 percent in nominal terms,
or 17.4 percent when measured at constant market prices.
</P>
<P>
The gross value of construction work performed by contractors
at locations other than construction sites amounted to 29.2
billion HK dollars (3.77 billion US dollars) in nominal terms,
11.2 percent higher than 1995.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the fourth quarter of 1996, the gross value of
construction work performed by main contractors for the same
period of 1995 increased by 15.1 percent in nominal terms.
</P>
<P>
When measured at constant market (1990) prices, it represented
an increase of 7.8 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
