relationship, the cornerstone for bilateral friendly relations,
has developed rapidly over the past few years, and bilateral trade
volume witnessed an annual increase rate of over 20 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Australian government's policy on Asia and China's reform
and opening policy have turned the two countries into important
trade and investment partners, and both are highly attentive to
bilateral cooperation of mutual benefit, Zhu said, adding that
this is encouraging.
</P>
<P>
Zhu also briefed Howard on the reform and development of
China's economy, overseas investment and finance.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Zhu and Howard heard plans of Australian
entrepreneurs to further bilateral cooperation in energy, mining
industry, finance, insurance and livestock products.
</P>
<P>
They also discussed cooperative possibilities in environmental
protection, sanitation, wool products and tourism.
</P>
<P>
Both Zhu and Howard hold that the two governments should
further encourage their business people to strengthen mutual
cooperation in various industries, while facing the international
market and raising bilateral economic and trade relations to a new
level.
</P>
<P>
This evening, Howard met here with Vice-Minister of State
Education Commission Wei Yu and dozens of students from
Beijing University.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Howard said that Australia and China can
strengthen cooperation in the cultural field, so as to enhance
mutual understanding and lay a better foundation for bilateral
cooperation in the future.  
