<HEADLINE> One More Palestinian Killed By Israelis in West Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 1 (Xinhua) -- One more Palestinian university
student was killed by Israeli soldiers in the West Bank today,
according to a report of JMCC, a Palestinian press service based
in East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The Al-Najah University student, the third Palestinian youth
killed by Israeli soldiers with a week, was participating in an
anti-Israeli demonstration near Qouseen Village at the junction
between Nablus and Qalqilya.
</P>
<P>
During the clashes between the Palestinian protesters and
Israeli solders, the student, whose name is not yet identified,
was killed and 11 others were injured by live ammunition and tear
gas fired by Israeli sodliers.
</P>
<P>
Kamel Sidqi Zarou, a 20-year-old resident of Hebron, was
shot dead by Israeli soldiers near the Kiryat Arba Settlement
outside Hebron earlier today.
</P>
<P>
On Saturday, Abdullah Salah, a 20-year-old Bir Zeit University
student of engineering, was killed by Israeli gunshots at the
Arak Checkpoint near the West Bank city of Ramallah.
</P>
<P>
Today's killings came after Arab League foreign ministers
recommended, at their annual meeting in the Egyptian capital of
Cairo Monday, the Arab states to cease the normalization of
relations with Israel and restore the economic boycott of the
Jewish state.
</P>
<P>
The decision shows that the Arab-Israeli relations, the
Palestinian-Israeli ties in particular, have sunk into a deep
crisis as a result of the Israeli government's policy of
settlement.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli government last month gave the green light to the
ground-breaking of 6,500 new Jewish homes in Har Homa of East
Jerusalem, arousing protest and anger of the Arabs and the
Palestinians in particular. The Palestinians want to have
Jerusalem as the capital of their future independent Palestinian
state. 
</P>
</TEXT>
