<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, April 1 (Xinhua) -- A new railway station serving as a
hub of the Hefei Railway went into operation today in Hefei,
capital of east China's Anhui Province.
</P>
<P>
The newly-built station, with a floor space of 33,182 square
meters, is one of the state key construction projects.
</P>
<P>
Total project investment was 583 million yuan (about 70 million
US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The station can now handle 5,000 passengers at a time, and 36
pairs of trains daily. It is expected to handle 60 pairs of trains
and 41,000 passengers daily later.
</P>
<P>
Twenty computerized ticket offices sell tickets to Beijing,
Shanghai, Guangzhou, Ningbo, Chengdu, Xiamen and Anqing. 
