<HEADLINE> At Least 24 Killed in Train Accidents in Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Two trains derailed in Spain within
10 hours from Monday night to Tuesday morning, killing at least 24
people and injuring more than 100, press reports said today.
</P>
<P>
The first train, which carried 248 passengers returning from
the Easter holidays, jumped the rails near the city of Pamplona in
northern Spain. The derailing was due to high speed.
</P>
<P>
At least 22 were killed instantly, while about 100 others were
injured and rushed to hospital.
</P>
<P>
The other train went out of the rail in the province of
Guadalajara, east of Madrid. At least two passengers were killed
and more than 20 injured. The cause of the accident is still
unknown.
</P>
<P>
The two accidents are Spain's most dreadful train disasters in
the past 20 years, officials said. 
</P>
