<HEADLINE> Kevin Johnson Named NBA Player of Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Kevin Johnson of the Phoenix Suns
was on Tuesday named the Nation Basketball Association (NBA)
player of the Week for last week.
</P>
<P>
Johnson led Phoenix to a 4-0 record during the week by
averaging 27.5 points, 9.0 assists and 3.8 rebounds per game, the
NBA said in a press release.
</P>
<P>
He was .480 (12 for 25) from three-point range and .968 (30 for
31) from the free throw line. He ranked fourth in scoring and tied
for eighth in assists among league leaders for the week.
</P>
<P>
Johnson began the week's competition last Tuesday with 28
points, 10 assists, six rebounds and two blocked shots as Phoenix
beat Milwaukee 117-112.
</P>
<P>
The 10-year veteran made a career high six three-point field
goals last Wednesday, had a game-high 31 points as the Suns won at
Seattle and had a season-high 38 points in the victory against
Golden State on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Phoenix, which began the season 0-13, had won six consecutive
games and has the seventh-best record (33-39) din the Western
Conference, two games behind Minnesota.
</P>
<P>
If Phoenix maintains its position and qualifies for the
playoffs, the Suns will surpass the 1967-68 Chicago Bulls (0-9)
and 1984-85 Cleveland Cavaliers (0-9) for the worst start in NBA
history for any team that proceeded to make the playoffs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
