<HEADLINE> Share Prices Up Marginally on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed mixed on the
Singapore market with the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index rising marginally to gain 1.67 points to close at 2074.67
points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume increased to 134.58 million units,
valued at 327.17 million Singapore dollars (about 227.2 million US
dollars). Declines outnumbered advances by 222 to 110, while 272
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong Land was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 4.62 million units. It was followed by
UIC which had 3.77 million of its shares traded. Amsteel warrant
was next with 3.21 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign led the gainers of
the day as it rose by 60 cents to finish at 26.9 Singapore
dollars. Creative 50 gained 50 cents to end at 13.6 Singapore
dollars, while the Development Bank of Singapore (DBS) Foreign and
local beverage maker F&AMP;N increased by 40 cents each to close at
17.2 and 12.2 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, the United Overseas Bank (UOB) Foreign A was
the biggest loser as it declined by 60 cents to end at 14.4
Singapore dollars. Samanda Holdings fell by 45 cents to 8.6
Singapore dollars, while Parkway warrant98 finished 42 cents lower
at 3.68 Singapore dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
