<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Closes Slightly Higher On Japanese </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar closed
slightly firmer as buying by Japanese names strengthened the
currency while Commonwealth bond prices fell because of fears of
higher US interest rates.
</P>
<P>
The local unit closed at 78.77 US cents from 78.63 at
Thursday's close.
</P>
<P>
The increase last week in US interest rates has narrowed the
difference between US official rate, now 5.5 percent, and the
official Australian rate of 6.0 percent.
</P>
<P>
This has led to speculation that Australian securities will be
less attractive, lessening demand for the Australian dollar.
</P>
<P>
But traders said, there had been demand for the currency by
Japanese names today, the first day of the new financial year in
Japan.
</P>
<P>
Against Japanese yen, the local unit ended at 97.37 from 97.16
and against Deutsche mark it was at 1.3150 from 1.3202.  
</P>
