<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 1 (Xinhua) -- At least 33 people had died on
Zimbabwe's roads by yesterday evening, taking the toll to almost
twice last year's 17, according to statistics from the police
general headquarters.
</P>
<P>
Another 197 people had been reported injured in about 389 road
traffic accidents since the beginning of the Easter holiday rush
throughout the country on Thursday.
</P>
