<HEADLINE> Chinese Bank's Commercialization Efforts Successful </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of Communications, which
was founded in 1908 and re-established in 1987, has had some
remarkable achievements in commercializing its operations by
focusing on management, quality, and risk-control.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1996, the bank's assets stood at 397.88 billion
yuan, with its deposits totaling 251.96 billion yuan, and loans,
179.16 billion yuan, bank sources say.
</P>
<P>
The bank has generated a total of 40 billion yuan in pre-tax
profits and paid 12.8 billion yuan in interest to stock-holders
over the past decade.
</P>
<P>
Since its rebirth, the bank has worked hard at becoming a
modern commercial bank, a senior bank official said. It is the
first in the country to be owned by central and local governments
as well as by a number of state-owned institutions and enterprises.
</P>
<P>
He said that it has set up a managerial system that is in line
with commercial bank requirements. It has the final say on its
internal affairs, its management, profit and loss, risk-control,
and financial operations, he said.
</P>
<P>
The bank has local branches in 89 major cities and over 2,400
business offices in these cities. It also has four overseas
branches and two representative offices, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
