<HEADLINE> HK, Myanmar Drug Dealers Sentenced to Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 1 (Xinhua) -- A Hong Kong man and a Myanmar man
involved in a drug trafficking case in 1993 have been sentenced to
death recently, the Thai news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Leet Yuan Wkung, 40, from Hong Kong, Chu Chin Kuay, 27, from
Myanmar, and a Thai national, were given the verdict by the Thai
criminal court on Monday for possessing a total of 34,589 grams of
heroin with the intent to sell, the Thai official news agency
said.
</P>
<P>
The three men were arrested on February 6, 1993 when police
found them sitting in a car in front of a department store in
Bangkok with a briefcase containing 100 bags of condensed heroin.
</P>
<P>
