<HEADLINE> Pak Lower House Repeals Controversial Portions of 8th </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's National Assembly
adopted here today without dissent the 13th amendment bill to
repeal the controversial portions of the 8th Constitutional
Amendment.
</P>
<P>
The bill, moved by Syed Zafar Ali Shah, Parliamentary Secretary
of the Pakistan Muslim League (N), aims at restoring the
constitutional powers of the Prime Minister, traditionally enjoyed
by the Chief Executive under a parliamentary system.
</P>
<P>
The bill was passed by the Assembly by 190 votes to nil.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the bill was adopted by the Senate with 79 votes in
favor to none against.  
