<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Industrial Base in Southernmost Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, April 1 (Xinhua) -- A new industrial base in the
suburbs of Haikou, the capital of China's island province of
Hainan, has become a multi-purpose economic development area for
the provincial export-oriented economy.
</P>
<P>
Five years of infrastructure construction at a cost of 600
million yuan has given some help to the investment environment in
the Guilinyang Industrial Base, equipping it with transportation,
energy, telecoms, and water facilities.
</P>
<P>
The zone generated nearly 1.9 billion yuan in output value and
400 million yuan in pre-tax profits in 1996. It now has 192
projects, 103 of which are under construction, and 47 that have
gone into operation in the fields of machine-building, building
materials, biology, textiles, electronics, and pharmaceuticals.
</P>
<P>
An investment fair scheduled for the 7th to the 10th of this
month is expected to help attract investment for construction of
more than 200 projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
