<DOCNO> XIE19970401.0160 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> College Girl Receives Big Insurance Indemnity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 1 (Xinhua) -- A Shanghai college student,
suffering from severe aplastic anaemia, has received 220,000 yuan
in compensation, from the local branch of the PICC Life.
</P>
<P>
The PICC Life is one of the three subsidiaries of the People's
Insurance Company of China, the country's biggest insurer.
</P>
<P>
This is one of the largest indemnities paid by Chinese
insurance companies over the past few years.
</P>
<P>
The 21-year-old student, named Wan Lili, was admitted into the
Shanghai College of Chemical Engineering for professional training
in September, 1995. She was diagnosed with the disease half a year
later.
</P>
<P>
Fortunately, Wan paid 36 yuan to buy a medicare insurance
policy on a two-year-term from the PICC Life Shanghai branch on
the day she entered the college.
</P>
<P>
Otherwise, her old father would have spent all his savings to
pay his daughter's medical costs.
</P>
<P>
The PICC Life Shanghai branch has paid 222,000 yuan to the girl
from last February to now.
</P>
<P>
The insurance company will have to pay about 100,000 yuan more
to the girl before this September for hospital expenses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
