<HEADLINE> Chinese President Hails AT&AMP;T Optical Cable Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 1 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin today hailed
the signing of a memorandum of understanding on a submarine
optical cable project between the US's AT&AMP;T and China.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with AT&AMP;T's Chairman Robert Allen in Beijing
today, Jiang wished the Sino-American project smooth sailing and
praised AT&AMP;T for having established good cooperative ties with
China over the past several years.
</P>
<P>
AT&AMP;T has made a positive contribution to Sino-US cooperation in
telecommunications and other fields, Jiang added.
</P>
<P>
Allen, who came for the signing ceremony at the invitation of
the Chinese Ministry of Posts and Telecommunications, briefed
Jiang on AT&AMP;T's business developments in China. He noted that
China's rapid economic growth, especially in telecommunications,
has gotten investment from many foreign companies.
</P>
<P>
Allen told Jiang that his current visit has been "very
successful" and that AT&AMP;T is ready to expand mutually beneficial
cooperation with China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
