<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Insurance Service Launched in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 1 (Xinhua) -- China has started pilot
operation of a new insurance service for civil engineering
projects in the Changning District of Shanghai, China's largest
city.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai is also one of the two pilot cities in China to open to
overseas insurance companies.
</P>
<P>
The new insurance service covers all risks that might happen
during construction of the projects. The total cost of the policy
will not exceed 0.25 percent of the overall investment of each
project.
</P>
<P>
China has never before had insurance coverage that includes
accidental life insurance, third party liability insurance and
property insurance within a single policy.
</P>
<P>
Changning District now has about 500 construction sites, and
the new insurance service has been applauded by builders of the
projects.
</P>
<P>
The local government of Changning has also adopted a rule that
all project builders must buy an insurance policy for their
projects before construction begins.
</P>
<P>
Insurance specialists say the service has a bright future,
since China has massive construction work in urban areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
