<HEADLINE> Big Loan To Assist Chinese Petrochemical Giant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 1 (Xinhua) -- One of China's biggest
petrochemical companies, the Shanghai Petrochemical Co. Ltd, has
received another 300 million yuan in bank loan for an ambitious
expansion project.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai branch of the Bank of Communications is providing
the loan to help the company become an ethylene production base
with an annual capacity of more than one million tons.
</P>
<P>
The bank branch, which follows a state industrial policy of
strongly supporting enterprise groups, has lent a total of 700
million yuan to the state-owned petrochemical producer so far.
