<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambian Government Overdraws Bank Account by $39 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian government has
overdrawn its account at the Bank of Zambia by 51.236 billion
Kwacha (about 39 million U.S. Dollars), representing heavy
borrowing from the banking system.
</P>
<P>
According to Bank of Zambia Monetary Survey/Statistics,
Zambia's domestic debt has been increasing, reflecting heavy
dependence on domestic money by the government to meet its
short-term expenditure requirements.
</P>
<P>
The increase in domestic debt has always brought negative
effects on the overall economy and with the high interest rates,
most government revenue has been going to service interest on
domestic debt.
</P>
<P>
Last year the government spent 122 billion Kwacha (about 94
million Dollars) on interest payments on the domestic debt.
</P>
<P>
As a result, most capital projects did not take off last year
due to the increasing domestic debt.
</P>
<P>
Economic analysts predicted that the government will be forced
to increase the allocation to domestic debt service this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
