<DOCNO> XIE19970401.0171 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai To Provide Residents With Tap Water Suitable for Drinking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Residents in No. 450 alley in
Baoshan street, Shanghai, can now drink water directly from the
tap, thanks to a drinking water renovation project for residential
buildings.
</P>
<P>
The project equips residential buildings with pure water
treatment facilities, then pipes the water suitable for drinking
to every household.
</P>
<P>
Upon completion of the whole project, every household will have
two kinds of taps, one for ordinary water, the other for pure
drinking water. The amount of water consumed will be recorded
separately by two water meters.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Tube Pure Water Company Ltd. is in charge of the work.
</P>
<P>
The manager of the marketing department of the company, Xu
Ming, said that although the renovation project cost every
household 1,000 yuan (about 120 US dollars), they can enjoy the
drinking water at the price of 0.3 yuan per kg, only about 40
percent of that of barreled pure water available in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai residents are more concerned with the quality of
drinking water, with almost ten percent of residents drinking
barreled pure water.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Tube Pure Water Company Ltd, established last
September, is constructing seven pure water piping projects, with
nearly 20 more such projects under negotiations. Most are part of
the construction plans of new residential buildings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
