<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Fall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
dropped sharply today as two days of losses on the New York Stock
Exchange and a sharp fall on the Australian sharemarket set the
tone.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 index ended 29 points lower at 2207 with a turnover
of 54 million NZ dollars (37 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Fletcher Challenge led the fall with all its shares declined.
Fletcher Building was down 11 cents to 417 cents, Fletcher Energy
down 5c to 383c, Fletcher Forests down 7c to 181c, Fletcher Paper
down 6c to 285c.
</P>
<P>
Among other leaders, Air New Zealand dropped 6c to 253c,
Brierley Investment lost 5c to 129c, Carter Holt Harvey dipped 3c
to 302c, and Telecom dived 5c to 650c. Lion Nathan was the only
leader holding the ground, finishing unchanged at 342c.
</P>
<P>
Overall, there were 8 rises and 83 falls.  
</P>
