<HEADLINE> Zambia Warns Infiltrating Zairean Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian government has warned
that Zairean government soldiers who wandered into Zambia should
surrender themselves to local authorities or return to their
country, otherwise, Zambia would be compelled to deal with them.
</P>
<P>
The Zambian government is keenly monitoring events in Luapula
Province where a number of heavily armed Zairean soldiers have
been spotted at a fishing camp near Mwense, said Defense Minister
Ben Mwila to local press on Monday.
</P>
<P>
"We are going to deal with these soldiers but I cannot say
what action we are going to take for security reasons. I want to
assure the people that the government is definitely going to do
something," he said.
</P>
<P>
Mwila is expected to go to Mansa, capital of Luapula Province,
this week to obtain first hand information on the issue.
</P>
<P>
He said that the government faced a similar situation in
Mpulungu Port by Lake Tangakyika recently and it took measures to
compel the Zairean soldiers to hand themselves over to
immigration officers.
</P>
<P>
Luapula Province Permanent Secretary Maybin Mubanga said that
the Zairean soldiers have been camped at a primary school and the
authorities there are cautious to approach them. 
</P>
</TEXT>
