<HEADLINE> Hebei Chamber of Commerce Plays Key Role in International Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The non-governmental
chambers of commerce in north China's Hebei Province have played
an active role in attracting business and expanding trade
relations with other countries.
</P>
<P>
Hebei now has 12 trade councils, and 56 counties have
set up councils for promoting international trade.
</P>
<P>
An official with the provincial government said that in 1996,
Hebei organized 30 trade talk trips to 19 countries and regions,
including Belgium, France, the United States, Canada and Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
Last year the Hebei Provincial Chamber of International Trade
signed cooperation agreements with its 16 counterparts in other
countries.
</P>
<P>
The Hebei Provincial Council for Promoting International Trade
has built a global trade network. It has opened an electronics
advertising business, and issued ads for 13 enterprises, getting
feedback from the United States, East Asia and Europe.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the trade chambers have helped local enterprises
and overseas businessmen seal 107 contracts, bringing in over 100
million yuan (about 12 million US dollars) in foreign investment,
with a business volume of 480 million US dollars.  
</P>
