<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, March 31 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Secretary-General Kofi Annan's special envoy Mohamed Sahnoun will
lead talks between Zaire's government and rebels, which are
scheduled for this weekend in South Africa, according to a
U.N. spokesman today.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman, Fred Eckhard, said that Sahnoun will conduct the
negotiations and the South African government will provide
logistical and other support for the talks.
</P>
