enhancement of women's status to ensure their full participation
in the country's endeavors for development, Myanmar leader Khin
Nyunt was quoted by today's official newspaper the New Light of
Myanmar as saying.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening session of a five-day working group
meeting on women's health and development here on Monday, Khin
Nyunt, who is the First Secretary of the Myanmar State Law and
Order Restoration Council, said "Equal rights and opportunities
are birth rights for women in Myanmar. And Myanmar traditions and
customs, the customary law, religious beliefs and practices have
all safeguarded the equality of Myanmar women in matrimony,
inheritance and society."
</P>
