<HEADLINE> Overseas-Backed Businesses in Yantai Profitable </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANTAI, April 1 (Xinhua) -- After years of operation,
overseas-funded enterprises in Yantai, a coastal city in east
China's Shandong province, have begun to see a return on their
investment.
</P>
<P>
Yantai now has 1,750 overseas-funded enterprises, 90 percent of
which are showing a profit. In 1996, overseas-funded enterprises
paid half the total industrial taxes in Yantai, while two-thirds
of the city's foreign exchanges were earned by overseas-funded
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Cheng Xiancui, director of the Yantai City Commission of
Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation, said that overseas
investors increased investment with their increased returns.
</P>
<P>
In the past two years, over 300 overseas-funded enterprises
have increased their investment. 
</P>
