<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Association Set up for Scientific Cooperation Across Taiwan Straits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, April 1 (Xinhua) -- An association for scientific and
technological exchanges and cooperation on both sides of the Taiwan
Straits was established in Xiamen, a coastal city in east China's
Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
Wang Rong, Xiamen vice-mayor and president of the association,
said the association's aim is to promote scientific and
technological exchanges and cooperation across the straits to help
build science and technology markets on both sides.
</P>
<P>
He said the association will arrange visits by scientists and
researchers and academic exchanges, and will provide information
for Taiwan scientists and researchers who come to the inland areas
for research. It will also encourage Taiwan investment in
high-tech industries in Xiamen, which is separated from Taiwan by
the sea.
</P>
<P>
So far. the association has 15 institutional members and over
140 individual members.
</P>
<P>
Xiamen is one of five ports open to Taiwan, and a large number
of Taiwan compatriots come to the inland via Xiamen. It has
approved 1,375 Taiwan-backed businesses involving 2.89
billion U.S. dollars in Taiwan investment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
