<HEADLINE> Foreign Amateur Actors In Chinese Films Criticized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The performances of some foreign
amateur actors in Chinese films and TV dramas have been criticized
by "China Culture News."
</P>
<P>
The paper, run by the Ministry of Culture, said that, as the
cultural sector opens wider to the outside world, a greater number
of foreign actors and actresses have been hired for Chinese films
and TV programs.
</P>
<P>
Many of them have even played famous historical figures in
films with an international theme, the paper added.
</P>
<P>
However, because most were not professional artists, their
performances were second- or third-rate, and did not meet with the
Chinese audience's expectations, the paper pointed out.
</P>
<P>
It suggested that film and TV departments improve contacts with
foreign film and TV institutes, and try to attract better
stars. But there is a problem with a shortage of funds, and the
enormous amounts famous foreign actors get for starring roles.
</P>
</TEXT>
