<HEADLINE> Southwest China Province Works Hard in Water Conservation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Sichuan
Province, the country's most populous province, has invested 2.27
billion yuan on water conservation projects so far this year, 1.6
times that of the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Observers say that Sichuan made unprecedented efforts in water
conservation this year, with major provincial officials working
with up to 15 million people on more than 1.03 million projects in
water conservation.
</P>
<P>
The province has repaired 680,000 km of dykes, planted 100,000
ha of trees, among its accomplishments.
</P>
<P>
The mountainous province is prone to floods because rainfall is
concentrated in July and August every year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
