<HEADLINE> Air China Opens Beijing-Hong Kong-London Flight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Air China's first Beijing-Hong
Kong-London flight began service today, providing the first air
link by a Chinese carrier between Beijing and a European city via
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The new route will provide further options for passengers
traveling on the Beijing-Europe route, said Air China President
Yin Wenlong.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Boeing 747-400 jumbo jets will be used on the
flight, which is scheduled for every Monday and Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Air China, China's leading carrier, now has 11 routes between
China and Europe.  
</P>
