<HEADLINE> East China City Promotes Hi-tech Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The capital of east China's Anhui
Province will start a hi-tech project to promote local economic
development, with 10 billion yuan in annual income expected in
industries that apply technology to production and market their
hi-tech products by the end of this century.
</P>
<P>
An additional two billion yuan in annual profits will be made
by local township enterprises with up-to-date equipment, and an
additional output value of one billion yuan of agricultural
production by using technology and using quality seeds is expected.
</P>
<P>
To reach this goal, the city will try to increase the
proportion of hi-tech industry in the local economy, accelerate
the transformation of large and medium-sized state enterprises,
improve management and technological level of township
enterprises, and popularize the use of technology and quality
seeds in rural areas. 
