<HEADLINE> Shanghai Consumer Goods Market Brisk </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Consumer goods sales in China's
largest metropolis saw a substantial increase as prices remained
stable in the first quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
In the first two months, consumer goods retail sales were worth
22.87 billion yuan, a jump of 16.5 percent over the same period of
last year. Sales for the first quarter are expected to reach
33.5 billion yuan, a year-on-year rise of 16.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
Retail prices of consumer goods are expected to edge up by
about two percent in the first three months.
</P>
<P>
Municipal officials attribute the sales boom to successful
marketing of goods during the New Year and Spring Festival holiday
periods. 
</P>
