<HEADLINE> Over 500 Die in Easter Holidays in Central America </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, March 31 (Xinhua) -- About 500 people died during the
Easter holidays in Central America and most of them were killed by
traffic accidents, violence or drowning, said reports reaching
here today.
</P>
<P>
There were 221 deaths reported in EL Salvador, 135 in Honduras,
70 in Nicaragua, 56 in Guatemala and 21 in Costa Rica.
</P>
<P>
Of the fatalities in El Salvador, 68 were killed by gunshots or
sharp instruments, 39 in traffic accidents, 28 by drowning and 86
for unknown causes. A total of 2,127 people were injured.
</P>
<P>
Honduras had 135 deaths during this period, 34 fewer than the
same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
In Guatemala, 21 of the fatalities were blamed on traffic
accidents and another 300 people were injured.
</P>
<P>
In Costa Rica, highway accidents were the main cause of
fatalities.  
</P>
