<HEADLINE> Chinese Government Increases Disaster Relief to Xinjiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, April 1 (Xinhua) -- China's central government has
given Xinjiang more than 76 million yuan this year to help the
disaster-affected areas rehabilitate their homeland, and ensure
normal life and production. More money is expected to follow.
</P>
<P>
Northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region was plagued
by frequent disasters in the past two years. Snowstorms hit Altay
and Ili prefectures in northern Xinjiang, while quakes shook
Jiashi County in the south this January, leaving dozens of
casualties and causing heavy losses.
</P>
<P>
