<HEADLINE> Guangdong Real Estate Business Thriving </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 1 (Xinhua) -- While the investment craze in
real estate in south China's Guangdong Province has cooled, sales
of buildings are mounting.
</P>
<P>
The southern province, an economic powerhouse in China, poured
58 billion yuan into development of real estate projects last
year, up five percent from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The total area of the land covered by the projects underway was
also marginally reduced, down 46 percent from 1995 to stand at
4,800 hectares.
</P>
<P>
However, the sales of buildings increased by 13 percent from
1995, and purchase prices rose slightly.
</P>
<P>
Most of the 32 billion yuan-worth of buildings sold were
apartments for ordinary urban dwellers.
</P>
<P>
As a result of China's stable economic growth and Hong Kong's
midnight handover on June 30, the prices of buildings for sale has
increased by five to 15 percent. 
