<HEADLINE> Indonesia's 1996/97 Inflation Declines to 5.17 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's inflation rate in
fiscal year 1996/97 (from April 1 to March 31) reached 5.17
percent, lower than the 8.86 percent for fiscal 1995/96, a senior
official said.
</P>
<P>
The inflation rate for fiscal 1996/97 was a record low since
fiscal 1985/86, Antara news agency reported today quoting Finance
Minister Mar'ie Mohamad.
</P>
<P>
While in the last two months the food sector was the biggest
contributor to inflation in the country, in March this sector
along with the sector of multifarious goods and services curbed
the inflation rate, turning it into a deflation of 0.12 percent,
the minister told local press on Monday.
</P>
<P>
With the 0.12 percent deflation, this year's inflation till
March reached 1.96 percent, lower than in the same period of last
year, reaching 3.26 percent, Mar'ie added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
