<HEADLINE> Indonesia Approves 6.3 Billion US Dollar FDI </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian government has
approved 6.3 billion US dollar foreign direct investment (FDI)
between January and March 15 this year, a cabinet minister said.
</P>
<P>
State Minister for Investment Sanyoto Sastrowardoyo said here
last night after meeting President Soeharto that for the same
period the approved domestic investment reached 35.3 trillion
rupiah (14.6 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
The foreign investment consisted of 191 projects, while the
domestic one was for 146 projects, the minister said.
</P>
<P>
Japan was the largest investor with 28 projects, followed by
the United States, Britain, Germany and Sweden, said
Sastrowardoyo.
</P>
<P>
Total foreign investment in Indonesia for 1996 was 29.9 billion
 dollars, a decrease from 1995's 39.9 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that total foreign investment approved in the
three fiscal years, starting in April 1994 and ending this month,
reached 100.6 billion dollars while the domestic amount reached
about 100.3 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, the realization rate of foreign direct
investment projects from calendar years 1990 to 1994 was only 53.8
percent, while for domestic projects it was 56.3 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
