<HEADLINE> 12 Philippine Cabinet Officials Eyeing Elective Posts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 1 (Xinhua) -- At least 12 members of the
Philippine Cabinet are planning to run for elective government
posts ranging from the presidency to congressional seats in the
1998 polls.
</P>
<P>
Today's local press said some of these Cabinet members have
already served notice that they will quit their Cabinet posts by
the middle of the year to enable them to concentrate on their
election campaign.
</P>
<P>
The Presidential Palace said Monday that a major Cabinet revamp
is inevitable once the department heads start filing their
certificates of candidacy for the 1998 local and national
elections.
</P>
<P>
Cabinet members intending to run for the presidency are Vice
President Joseph Estrada, Defense Secretary Renato de Villa,
Finance Secretary Roberto de Ocampo and Presidential Adviser on
Economic Affairs Emilio Osmena, local newspapers said.
</P>
<P>
Presidential Assistant on Political Affairs Gabriel Claudio
said to fill up the posts to be vacated are career executives or
undersecretaries and nominees from the private sector.
</P>
<P>
He added that the ruling Lakas-NUCD party will hold a
convention to select its national candidates whose names will be
announced not later than 120 days before the elections in 1998.
</P>
<P>
President Fidel Ramos repeated that he would not seek a second
term, but some Filipinos still do not believe that he would step
down as his term ends in 1998.  
</P>
</TEXT>
