opening-day action, struggled early but survived with a 4-6, 6-4,
6-4 victory over Canadian qualifier Rene Simpson.
</P>
<P>
Hard-serving Dutchwoman Brenda Schultz-McCarthy, seeded 14th,
had all she could handle from Elena Makarova.
</P>
<P>
The Russian, ranked a lowly 93rd in the world, kept
Schultz-McCarthy on court for two hours and 20 minutes before the
14th seed finally prevailed 3-6, 7-6 (7-2), 6-4.
</P>
<P>
The strong field is headed by 16-year-old Swiss sensation
Martina Hingis, who will play her first match as the number one
player in the world on Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
Hingis, who takes five titles this year, opens against
Germany's Barbara Rittner in the second round after receiving a
first-round bye.
</P>
<P>
Monica Seles, who was crushed by Hingis in the Lipton
Championships final Saturday, also took part in the tournament.
