<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan-Shandong Joint Venture Signed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, April 1 (Xinhua)-- A contract to build a
superphosphate joint venture between Kazakhstan and east China's
Shandong Province was signed here recently.
</P>
<P>
Under the contract, a chemical venture will be built in
Kazakhstan with waste materials discharged by local superphosphate
works as raw materials.
</P>
<P>
It will produce 200,000 tons of sulphuric acid and 300,000 tons
of cement annually when it starts operation.
</P>
<P>
The Lubei Chemical Group in Shandong Province will provide the
design and equipment for the venture, and train technicians and
workers. 
