<HEADLINE> Maradona: Fight Against Drug is Constant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Diego Maradona said on
Monday his fight against drug addiction was a constant struggle
and he was desperately trying to give it up.
</P>
<P>
The 36-year-old Maradona, who had treatment for his drug
problem last year, said on Argentinian television that if it
wasn't for his wife Claudia he would have not considered giving up
drugs.
</P>
<P>
"She is the best mother in the world and thank God she is my
wife," Maradona said.
</P>
<P>
"Drugs breaks a family. It is like a 'PacMan' which eats up
love, your family and oneself," Maradona added.
</P>
<P>
He denied reports that it was his manager Guillermo Coppola,
who was recently acquitted on a drugs trafficking charge, who
turned him into an addict.
</P>
<P>
"I didn't even know Coppola when I started taking cocaine,"
Maradona said. 
</P>
