<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 4.8 Tons of Drugs Seized In Panama During First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Panama's anti-drug forces
confiscated 4.5 tons of drugs and arrested 250 suspected drug
traffickers during the first quarter of this year, said
authorities today.
</P>
<P>
Narcotics Division of the Judicial Technical Police said of
that total, 2.6 tons corresponded to cocaine and 1.6 tons to
marijuana, crack, bazuco and heroin.
</P>
<P>
In January, the authorities made 81 seizures of illegal
substances and detained 87 people; in February it made 71 seizures
and 86 arrests and up to March 23, it carried out 64 anti-drug
operations and took 77 people into custody.
</P>
<P>
The most important anti-narcotic operations carried out in the
quarter was made on March 22 when the police seized 1,339
kilograms of cocaine worth 33 million dollars hidden in tins of
preserves and being transported inside a truck in the city of
Chorrera, about 30 kilometers west of the capital.
</P>
<P>
During the operation, the police captured 11 people, including
four women.
</P>
<P>
Last week, the police confiscated 19 kilograms of cocaine and
detained four people in Chame, a city about 70 kilometers north of
the capital.
</P>
<P>
On February 4, anti-drug agents seized 1,118 kilograms of
cocaine worth 20 million dollars on the black market and arrested
four people in the Chanis, a neighborhood district in the capital.
</P>
<P>
According to official figures, the police in 1996 seized a
total of 22.4 tons of drugs including 18 tons of marijuana and
3.9 tons of cocaine. Some 1,225 people on drug-trafficking charges
were arrested.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, the police confiscated 8.5 tons of drugs and detained
882 people while 6.2 tons of drugs were seized and 962 people were
arrested in 1994 on drug-related charges. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
