<P>
BUENOS AIRES, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Argentine President Carlos
Menem met today with a Chinese military delegation headed by
General Zhang Wannian, vice-chairman of China's Central Military
Commission.
</P>
<P>
Menem spoke highly of the bilateral relations between Argentina
and China, emphasizing their cooperation in various fields during
the past few years.
</P>
<P>
Menem congratulated the Chinese government and people on
China's resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong
as of July 1 this year.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the solution of the Hong Kong issue is an
historic event which proclaims to the whole world that the
policy of colonization is out of date.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, Menem reiterated his condolences over the
death of Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping, highlighting his important
contributions to China.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Zhang reasserted his hope to promote the
bilateral relations between the two countries and their armed
forces.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese military delegation arrived here on Sunday for a
4-day visit to Argentina, the first stop of its South America
tour. The delegation will leave for Chile and then Brazil on April
4. 
