<HEADLINE> Expressway Being Built for Hangzhou And Huangshan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 1 (Xinhua) -- An expressway is under
construction between Hangzhou, a scenic city in east China's
Zhejiang Province and Huangshan Mountain, considered one of the
most beautiful peaks in China.
</P>
<P>
The 280-km expressway, which is built on the foundation of the
original highway, will shorten the trip from six hours by car to
two.
</P>
<P>
Huangshan is located in Anhui Province, which borders the
coastal province of Zhejiang in the west. Zhejiang and its
northern Jiangsu and Shanghai, which are all along China's eastern
coast, spearhead China's economic growth. 
</P>
