<HEADLINE> Slovakia Beat Malta in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Slovakia beat Malta 2-0 to draw
level on points with Yugoslavia in World Cup qualifying group six
in Valletta, Malta on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Tibor Jancula put the Slovaks ahead in the 39th minute and
Dusan Tittel added the second two minutes into injury time.
</P>
<P>
The Maltese, weakened by the absence of four key players
through injury and suspension, were always on the defensive but
their reserve goalkeeper Mario Muscat was outstanding.
</P>
<P>
Jancula broke the deadlock late in the first half when he broke
almost from the halfway line and placed the ball beyond the reach
of the advancing Muscat.
</P>
<P>
Maltese defender Lawrence Attard was unlucky not to head home
from a corner a few minutes after the interval and Slovak keeper
Alexander Vancel saved a powerful shot from outside the box by
Joseph Brincat.
</P>
<P>
Ten minutes later Brincat beat Vancel only to see his goal
ruled offside.
</P>
<P>
Tittel scored Slovakia's second goal in injury time with a
header.
</P>
<P>
Slovakia lie joint second in the group, four points behind
leaders Spain. Malta have lost all six of their matches,
conceding 27 goals without scoring any. 
</P>
</TEXT>
