<HEADLINE> Tianjin Has New Banking Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 1 (Xinhua) -- A new banking service has been
put into trial operation in north China's port city of
Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
Account holders just need to dial a telephone number to report
the loss of checks or check their bank notes.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that this is the first banking service in China to
enhance bank note security with high technology.
</P>
<P>
The service is a computer network in which users can input
immediate information of the bank notes lost, blank checks
stolen, and checks issued or registered null.
</P>
<P>
The network can provide instant feedback if the bank notes are
being illegally used, and inform the police. 
</P>
</TEXT>
