<HEADLINE> US Dollar Slightly Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, March 31 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. dollar rose to end
slightly higher against most key currencies today, recovering from
a decline caused by another plunge in the U.S. stock market.
</P>
<P>
Traders attributed the dollar's comeback partly to the benefits
of rising interest rates and a growing economy.
</P>
<P>
But the same forces pushed the Dow Jones average down 157.11
points, or 2.3 percent, in the New York stock market.
</P>
